<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.1.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2020-11-11T23:57:45-06:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Testa Software</title><subtitle>The personal and professional home of Steve Testa</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Fastpages Notebook Blog Post</title><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/jupyter/2020/02/20/test.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fastpages Notebook Blog Post" /><published>2020-02-20T00:00:00-06:00</published><updated>2020-02-20T00:00:00-06:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/jupyter/2020/02/20/test</id><author><name></name></author><category term="jupyter" /><summary type="html"></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/images/chart-preview.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/images/chart-preview.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">An Example Markdown Post</title><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/markdown/2020/01/14/test-markdown-post.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="An Example Markdown Post" /><published>2020-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</published><updated>2020-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/markdown/2020/01/14/test-markdown-post</id><author><name></name></author><category term="markdown" /><summary type="html">Example Markdown Post</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Web Application Primer in Haskell - Web Framework</title><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/07/27/web-application-primer-in-haskell-web-framework.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Web Application Primer in Haskell - Web Framework" /><published>2017-07-27T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-07-27T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/07/27/web-application-primer-in-haskell-web-framework</id><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">There are plenty of choices when it comes to Haskell web frameworks: yesod, spock, snap, happstack - just to name a few. The Haskell Wiki provides a list of descriptions and differences between some of the web frameworks out there.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Web Application Primer in Haskell - Haskell</title><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/07/03/web-application-primer-in-haskell-programming-language.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Web Application Primer in Haskell - Haskell" /><published>2017-07-03T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-07-03T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/07/03/web-application-primer-in-haskell-programming-language</id><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">In this series, we’re going to work our way through the development stack bottom-up. So to kick off our Haskell web application primer we’re going to start with Haskell and core Game of Life code.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Web Application Primer in Haskell - Overview</title><link href="https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/06/23/web-application-primer-in-haskell.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Web Application Primer in Haskell - Overview" /><published>2017-06-23T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-06-23T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>https://testasoftware.github.io/2017/06/23/web-application-primer-in-haskell</id><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">In this upcoming series of posts we’re going to go over the end-to-end process on how to build and deploy a web application using Haskell. I use the term “web application” instead of “website” because the implication is that we’re building something more than just some static HTML and CSS. The intent is to build an actual application with dynamic front-end behavior that is in direct communication with the back-end code.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://testasoftware.github.io/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/haskell.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>